### 3.3 Concentric Corners Rule (Radii Nesting)
To maintain visual proportion, outer container corners must be styled concentrically relative to their children and inner padding. Use the formula:
$$\text{Outer Radius} = \text{Inner Radius} + \text{Padding}$$

*If the calculated target does not correspond to an existing token value, adjust the internal padding instead of using a non-standard radius value.*

