## 4. Accessibility & Compliance Requirements (WCAG 2.2 AA)

Compliance is a core brand constraint. Implement these programmatic rules during generation:

### 4.1 Surface-Aware Focus States
Avoid simple single-colored focus outlines, which can become invisible on contrasting backgrounds. Use a two-layer focus ring system:

```css
/* Standard focus implementation */
.focus-ring-target:focus-visible {
  outline: none;
  box-shadow: 
    0 0 0 2px var(--color-bg-surface), 
    0 0 0 4px var(--color-focus-ring);
}

/* Inverted style for primary-brand elements or dark container cards */
.on-brand-surface .focus-ring-target:focus-visible {
  outline: none;
  box-shadow: 
    0 0 0 2px var(--color-bg-brand), 
    0 0 0 4px var(--color-focus-ring-inverse);
}
```

### 4.2 Color as a Single Signal Prohibited
* Never convey system statuses (Success, Warning, Error) using color alone. 
* Combine color changes with illustrative iconography (e.g., checkmarks, warning flags) and explanatory text labels.
* Text links within body prose must use a clear underline element (`text-decoration: underline`), rather than relying only on text-color variation.

### 4.3 Interactive Touch Targets
* All buttons, interactive items, inputs, and links must have a minimum interactive layout target of `24x24px`. Provide a preference for `44x44px` on elements intended for mobile or tablet access.

### 4.4 Reduced Motion
Include standard motion suppression in global stylesheets to accommodate sensory-sensitive users:

```css
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  *, *::before, *::after {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    animation-iteration-count: 1 !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    scroll-behavior: auto !important;
  }
}
```

